            <V n="text" t="variation">
              <U n="variation">
                <L n="variations">
                  <T>0x96E5A780<!--Oh! You've heard the story about Moppy, that goat statue in Crow's Crossing, right? It's this whole local legend thing. Apparently some medieval nomads were off in search of sustenance when they ran into an odd woman who claimed she could read Tarot cards. Ravendancer, I think. The wandering souls were so enthralled by her that they felt as if they'd been enchanted. When they came across a goat, they thought it must be magical in some way and chased it instead of catching it to eat it. The goat led them to a bountiful land—this one! Over the years, the legend of Moppy—the goat who led them to good fortune—has been told over and over again.--></T>
                  <T>0xEAAD2033<!--Tziporah and I got married after she took ambrosia. She just really wasn't into being a ghost. I can't blame her—I sure don't want her to be one, either. I just wish she was a little bit less of a klutz. I feel like Grim's always just around the corner from our place.--></T>
                </L>
              </U>
            </V>
