            <V n="text" t="variation">
              <U n="variation">
                <L n="variations">
                  <T>0xFA7D76A<!--Each Sim has their own unique perspective on life and the life thereafter. Sometimes we want to be with those who reflect our beliefs back, but sometimes we also thrive in our differences while embracing our similarities. Tziporah's beliefs are somewhat different than my own, but we share so many other common values. I feel like she's a Sim I've known past my own life, if you understand what I mean.--></T>
                  <T>0xABFD9BE8<!--No one likes talking about end-of-life things, I get it. Though I like to think if we're honest about what matters to us, it helps our family more later on. That's why I always remind people that it's better to head over to the Town Hall sooner rather than later to meet up with an attorney to get your Will all sorted. It's easier than you think. --></T>
                </L>
